I also tried via a partial class, once I noticed the generated code makes partials, but that didn't make the compiler happy either.

From the tutorial (add a string Name attribute to the FooBar):

public interface FooBar {
string Name { get; }
}
public partial class FooBar : IFooBar {
//compiler complains about Name not being implemented, despite the generated code defining public virtual string Name { get ... set ... }
}
